modules.description: This module defines command-line arguments and converters for selecting PKCS#11 slots, tokens, and library loading options. It supports parsing values like slot index, slot ID, slot description, token label, PIN, and DLL name into typed Cmdliner arguments. These are used to configure PKCS#11 session parameters and library interaction modes when building command-line tools.

This module defines command-line interface terms for selecting PKCS#11 slots, tokens, and authentication parameters. It provides parsed values for slot index, ID, description, token label, PIN, load mode, and user type, ensuring mutual exclusivity when selecting slots. These terms are used to construct P11.Slot.t values and configure PKCS#11 session parameters directly from CLI arguments.

This module provides command-line interface components for configuring PKCS#11 operations through typed arguments and terms. It supports parsing and selecting slots, tokens, and authentication parameters such as slot index, ID, description, token label, PIN, and load mode, ensuring mutual exclusivity where applicable. The parsed values are used to construct P11.Slot.t values and configure session parameters directly in CLI-driven PKCS#11 tools. Example usage includes building commands that require authenticated access to a specific token or initializing a session with a given slot and PIN.
